 form they take, however, stories have the power to transport us to other places and times.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"This choice does not follow from the information given or contains a calculation error. Choice C is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"D","text":"Many cultures have developed unique forms of storytelling, and the ways in which these stories are told vary widely. For example, in some cultures, stories are told orally, while in others, stories are written down. Stories can also be passed down through generations, and they can be adapted or changed as they are passed on; whatever form they take, however, stories have the power to transport us to other places and times.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"The best way to combine the sentences in the paragraph is to use a semicolon to connect the first two sentences because the second sentence provides an example of the idea presented in the first. The semicolon is also used correctly to connect the third and fourth sentences because the fourth senten. Choice D matches the question''s requirement and is consistent with the passage''s central claim or supporting detail. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."}]'::jsonb,
